HEADWORD: Crossette
<hw>Cros*sette"</hw> <pr>(kr?s-s?t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., dim.
of <ets>crosse</ets>. See <er>Crosier</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A return in one of the corners of the architrave of a
door or window; -- called also <altname>ancon</altname>,
<altname>ear</altname>, <altname>elbow</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The shoulder of a joggled keystone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cross-eyed</ent>⟦br⟧
